    "description": [
        {
            "text": "Thermochemical Calorie per Cubic Meter Kelvin is a unit for Volumetric Heat Capacity expressed as cal_th/(m^3 K). Derived from the prefixed unit by removing the centi- prefix from the length factor in the denominator (cm^3 -> m^3). Relative to cal_th/(cm^3 K), magnitudes scale by 10^6. The SI conversion factor is 4.184 J/(m^3 K).",
